# Trivy ignore file — accepted, reviewed vulnerabilities.
# Reviewed: 2026-06-28. Re-evaluate when homey-api ships a socket.io-client v4+ release.
#
# CVE-2024-36751 — parseuri ReDoS.
# Reached only through homey-api's legacy socket.io-client@2.x realtime transport.
# This MCP server uses request/response HTTP calls, not the realtime socket, and the
# only socket peer is the user's own trusted local Homey Pro. homey-api pins
# socket.io-client@^2.5.0 and engine.io-client@^3.5.5, so the patched major cannot be
# adopted without breaking Homey connectivity. Severity in this context is low.
CVE-2024-36751
